---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Research & Advisory — Autonomy Bridge"
  description="Independent commercialization research for AI, robotics, industrial automation, and enterprise B2B SaaS. Market sizing, pricing validation, adoption risk, and commercial due diligence."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="container">
    <h1>Research &amp; Advisory</h1>
    <p class="subhead">Independent analysis for high-stakes technology decisions.</p>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What Autonomy Bridge Does</h2>
      <p>
        Autonomy Bridge produces decision-grade research at the intersection of advanced technology
        and enterprise adoption. The firm specializes in AI, robotics, industrial automation, and
        enterprise B2B SaaS—sectors where technical feasibility does not guarantee commercial success.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Commercialization Research</h2>
      <p>
        Commercialization research bridges the gap between "this technology works" and "this
        technology makes money." While traditional market research focuses on sentiment, our
        approach focuses on friction and economic reality.
      </p>
      <p>Core areas of focus:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Buyer Economics</strong> — Identifying the threshold where the solution becomes a financial "must-have."
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Adoption Friction</strong> — Documenting the operational and cultural barriers to deployment.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pilot-to-Production Risk</strong> — Mapping the "valley of death" between a successful test and a site-wide rollout.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Real-World Unit Economics</strong> — Modeling margins under actual operational constraints, not ideal laboratory conditions.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Research Products</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Market Opportunity &amp; Sizing Models</strong> —
          Proprietary models for TAM, SAM, and realistic serviceable demand including bottom-up reconciliation and sensitivity analysis.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Buyer &amp; ICP Research</strong> —
          Structured analysis of buying committees, stakeholder veto points, and the separation between technical interest and economic budget.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Pricing &amp; Business Model Validation</strong> —
          Comparative analysis of CAPEX, subscription, and RaaS (Robotics-as-a-Service) models against margin thresholds.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Competitive &amp; Ecosystem Mapping</strong> —
          Deep-dive analysis of direct competitors, indirect substitutes, and channel partner dynamics.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Adoption Risk Assessments</strong> —
          Documentation of technical debt, operational friction, regulatory hurdles, and deployment complexity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Commercial Due Diligence Reports</strong> —
          Structured assessments of market claims and commercialization hurdles for investment or acquisition decisions.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Advisory Support</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Executive Synthesis</strong> — Time-bound advisory focused on translating research into board-level strategy.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Decision Briefing</strong> — Direct consultation for CEOs and Product Leads to prioritize investments or GTM paths.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Constraint Identification</strong> — Strategic sessions to identify the "binding constraint" in a commercialization cycle.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What Clients Receive</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Decision Briefs</strong> — Concise, high-impact executive summaries.</li>
        <li><strong>Market &amp; Economic Models</strong> — Dynamic datasets with explicit, editable assumptions.</li>
        <li><strong>Presentation Decks</strong> — Visualized data for board and stakeholder communication.</li>
        <li><strong>Strategic Recommendations</strong> — Clear "Go/No-Go" logic based on identified trade-offs.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What We Don't Do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No Execution</strong> — No implementation, software development, or engineering work.</li>
        <li><strong>No Marketing Ops</strong> — No lead generation, content marketing, or sales collateral production.</li>
        <li><strong>No Staff Augmentation</strong> — No long-term, open-ended "extra hands" roles.</li>
        <li><strong>No Post-Hoc Validation</strong> — Research is not conducted to justify decisions already made.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
